com.storytron.uber.operator

Class Operator

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.storytron.uber.operator.Operator
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<Operator>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    CustomOperator, ParameterOperator, TraitOperator

    public class Operator
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<Operator>
    This class represents operators that appear in scripts.

    They contain a label, a return type and a list of arguments they expect. Each arguments defines a prompt, an expected type, and optionally a default value.

    Operators also can introduce in scope for their children an iterator like CandidateActor, CandidateStage, etc. In which case, the operator is said to be an iteration.
